
What should happen
Your script should:
    1. Initialize Vault 
    2. Unseal Vault 
    3. Login 
    4. Enable KV v2 at kv/
    5. Enable AppRole auth
    6. Create app-policy and admin-policy
    7. Create approle 
    8. Store a sample secret at kv/app/config
    9. Generate and save:
        ○ Unseal key and root token in init.txt
        ○ Role ID in setup/roles/app-role-id.txt
        ○ Secret ID in setup/roles/app-secret-id.txt

After running the script called **init-vault.sh**

Before running Vault CLI commands, set the Vault address:

export VAULT_ADDR="http://127.0.0.1:8200"

Note: if you want it permanent, save this is the /.bashrc file

“The script sets VAULT_ADDR for its own execution, but since environment variables don’t persist across shell sessions, set it in the terminal separately or in the shell profile.

✅ 1. Verify Vault is initialized
vault status

👉 Look for:

Initialized: true
Sealed: true

🔓 2. Unseal Vault 
Get your unseal key:
cat init.txt

👉 Copy:

Unseal Key 1: <value>
Unseal:
vault operator unseal <UNSEAL_KEY>
Verify:
vault status

👉 Now you should see:

Sealed: false
🔐 3. Login with root token
vault login

👉 Paste your root token from init.txt

✅ 4. Enable KV v2 at kv/

Check first:

vault secrets list

If kv/ is NOT there:

vault secrets enable -path=kv kv-v2

🔐 5. Enable AppRole auth

Check:

vault auth list

If not present:

vault auth enable approle

📜 6. Create policies
vault policy write app-policy ./setup/policies/app-policy.hcl
vault policy write admin-policy ./setup/policies/admin-policy.hcl

👤 7. Create AppRole
vault write auth/approle/role/app-role \
  token_policies="app-policy" \
  secret_id_ttl=60m \
  token_ttl=30m \
  token_max_ttl=60m

🔑 8. Get Role ID
vault read auth/approle/role/app-role/role-id

Save it:

vault read -format=json auth/approle/role/app-role/role-id \
  | jq -r '.data.role_id' > setup/roles/app-role-id.txt

🔑 9. Generate Secret ID
vault write -f auth/approle/role/app-role/secret-id

Save it:

vault write -format=json -f auth/approle/role/app-role/secret-id \
  | jq -r '.data.secret_id' > setup/roles/app-secret-id.txt

🔐 10. Store sample secret
vault kv put kv/app/config api_key="super-secret-api-key" env="dev"

🔍 11. Verify secret
vault kv get kv/app/config

📁 12. Verify files were created
cat init.txt
cat setup/roles/app-role-id.txt
cat setup/roles/app-secret-id.txt
